==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Measle
<hw>Mea"sle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>mesel</ets>,
OF. <ets>mesel</ets>, LL. <ets>misellus</ets>, L. <ets>misellus</ets>
unfortunate, dim. of <ets>miser</ets>. See <er>Miser</er>.]</ety> <def>A
leper.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <altsp>[Written also <asp>meazel</asp>,
and <asp>mesel</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Wyclif (Matt. x. 8.
).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Measle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Measle
<hw>Mea"sle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tapeworm
larva. See 2d <er>Measles</er>, 4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Measled</ent>⟦br⟧
